command=grep -n repository_layout.evidence_partition cairn/specs/repository-layout/spec.md
629:r[repository_layout.evidence_partition.scheme] Durable evidence under `docs/evidence/` SHOULD follow a documented partition scheme for receipts, run logs, manifests, generated indexes, oracle notes, and archived/historical artifacts.
633:r[repository_layout.evidence_partition.scheme.clear]
641:r[repository_layout.evidence_partition.inventory] Existing `docs/evidence/` artifacts MUST be inventoried before bulk movement or partition migration.
645:r[repository_layout.evidence_partition.inventory.citation]
653:r[repository_layout.evidence_partition.manifest_rules] Evidence manifest tooling MUST resolve partitioned durable evidence paths and reject stale, missing, target-only, result-only, or path-escaping entries.
657:r[repository_layout.evidence_partition.manifest_rules.valid]
665:r[repository_layout.evidence_partition.index] The repository SHOULD provide a reviewable evidence index mapping changes, scenarios, dates, and artifact classes to durable evidence paths.
669:r[repository_layout.evidence_partition.index.findable]
676:r[repository_layout.evidence_partition.guards] Partition migration MUST include guards or fixtures for stale manifests, broken citations, missing index rows, and unsafe paths.
680:r[repository_layout.evidence_partition.guards.broken]
688:r[repository_layout.evidence_partition.validation] Evidence partitioning MUST record evidence manifest checks, task evidence validation, index freshness checks, and Cairn gates before archive.
692:r[repository_layout.evidence_partition.validation.log]
